  "prompt": "Which are the best Hollywood movies based on history?",
  "response": "Hollywood has produced several remarkable movies based on historical events and figures. Here's a list of some of the best, known for their accuracy, storytelling, and cinematic quality:\n\n1. **Schindler's List (1993)**\n   - Directed by Steven Spielberg, this film depicts the true story of Oskar Schindler, a German businessman who saved the lives of over 1,000 Jewish refugees during the Holocaust by employing them in his factories.\n\n2. **Saving Private Ryan (1998)**\n   - Directed by Steven Spielberg, this film follows a group of U.S. soldiers during World War II as they search for a paratrooper whose brothers have been killed in action. It is renowned for its realistic portrayal of the D-Day invasion.\n\n3. **12 Years a Slave (2013)**\n   - Directed by Steve McQueen, this film is based on the memoir of Solomon Northup, a free black man from upstate New York who was abducted and sold into slavery in the pre-Civil War United States.\n\n4. **Lincoln (2012)**\n   - Directed by Steven Spielberg, this film focuses on the final months of Abraham Lincoln's life, particularly his efforts in January 1865 to have the Thirteenth Amendment to the United States Constitution passed by the United States House of Representatives.\n\n5. **The King's Speech (2010)**\n   - Directed by Tom Hooper, this film tells the story of King George VI, who, to overcome his stammer, works with an unorthodox speech therapist before his historic wartime broadcast.\n\n6. **Gladiator (2000)**\n   - Directed by Ridley Scott, this epic historical drama follows the fictional story of Maximus Decimus Meridius, a Roman general who becomes a gladiator after his family is murdered by the emperor's son.\n\n7. **A Beautiful Mind (2001)**\n   - Directed by Ron Howard, this film is based on the life of John Nash, a Nobel Laureate in Economics who struggled with schizophrenia.\n\n8. **Hidden Figures (2016)**\n   - Directed by Theodore Melfi, this film celebrates the contributions of three African-American women mathematicians working at NASA during the Space Race.\n\n9. **Amadeus (1984)**\n   - Directed by Milos Forman, this film is a fictionalized biography of Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart, told from the perspective of his rival, Antonio Salieri.\n\n10. **Gandhi (1982)**\n    - Directed by Richard Attenborough, this biographical film covers the life of Mohandas K. Gandhi, the leader of the Indian independence movement against British rule.\n\nThese films are celebrated for their historical significance, compelling narratives, and powerful performances. They provide a great starting point for anyone interested in historical cinema from Hollywood.",
